              <h2><a name="in_news"></a>Club Penguin in the News</h2>
            <p><a href="downloads/your-igloo-mine.pdf">Your Igloo or Mine?</a> (pdf)<br>
                <span class="sm_txt">Newsweek | Febuary 23, 2007</span><br>
                <br>
Web sites like Club Penguin have introduced social networking to children. Welcome to MySpace in braces.</p>
            <p align="right"><font size="2" face="Arial"><a href="downloads/your-igloo-mine.pdf"></a></font></p>
            <p align="left"><a href="downloads/surfins-safe-for-the-small-set.pdf">Surfin&rsquo;s Safe for the Small Set</a>  (pdf)<br>
              <span class="sm_txt">ContraCostaTimes.com | 
                Febuary 21, 2007</span><br>
                <br>
              Club Penguin&rsquo;s ad-free, monitored website meets a need for kid-safe spaces   online, and encourages creativity from young users in a virtual community that   combines game play and chat.</p>
            <p align="right"><font size="2" face="Arial"><a href="downloads/surfins-safe-for-the-small-set.pdf"></a></font></p>
            <p><a href="downloads/club-penguin-beckons-preteen-surfers.pdf"> Online, Club Penguin Beckons to Preteen Surfers</a>  (pdf)<br>
                  <span class="sm_txt">npr.org | 
                    January 19, 2007</span><br>
                              <br>
                Club Penguin offers safe Internet entry point for preteen, first-time web users   with their interactive site that supports safe chat, playing games and creating   online community.</p>
            <p align="right"><font size="2" face="Arial"><a href="downloads/club-penguin-beckons-preteen-surfers.pdf"></a></font></p>
            <p><a href="downloads/procession-penguins-arrives.pdf">A Procession of Penguins Arrive on Madison Ave.</a>  (pdf)<br>
                  <span class="sm_txt">nytimes.com | 
                    January 10, 2007</span><br>
                            <br>
                Penguins have become an icon of choice in popular culture-from online gaming, movies and advertising.</p>
            <p align="right"><font size="2" face="Arial"><a href="downloads/procession-penguins-arrives.pdf"></a></font></p>
            <p><a href="downloads/girls-just-want-to-have-fun-on-computers.pdf">Girls just want to have fun - on computers</a>  (pdf)<br>
                  <span class="sm_txt">ScrippsNews.com | 
                    January 4, 2007</span><br>
                              <br>
            Club Penguin is attracting more girls to the traditionally boy-dominated   industry. Betsy Hart discovers why it works for her daugters.</p>
            <p align="right">            <font size="2" face="Arial"><a href="downloads/girls-just-want-to-have-fun-on-computers.pdf"></a></font></p>
            <p><a href="downloads/children-penguins-turn-trio-into-kingpins.pdf">Children and penguins turn trio into kingpins</a>  (pdf)<br>
                  <span class="sm_txt">theglobeandmail.com | 
                    November 13, 2006</span></p>
              <p> One of Canada's leading daily newspapers features Club Penguin as a "virtual playground" for children describing how it got started, where it's going and how its values are shaping the company's directive.</p>
              <p align="right"><font size="2" face="Arial"><a href="downloads/children-penguins-turn-trio-into-kingpins.pdf"></a></font></p>
              <p><a href="downloads/homemaking-parenting-on-thin-ice.pdf">Homemaking: Parenting on thin ice</a>  (pdf)<br>
                  <span class="sm_txt">post-gazette.com |                        November 11, 2006</span><br>
                  <br>
                But you gotta at least hope, don't   you? One of them clued me in that they'd all joined "Club Penguin," an   online virtual world.</p>
              <p align="right"><font size="2" face="Arial"><a href="downloads/homemaking-parenting-on-thin-ice.pdf"></a> </font></p>
              <p><a href="downloads/How-young-is-too-young-for-MySpace.pdf">How young is too young for MySpace?</a>  (pdf)<br>
                  <span class="sm_txt">Moneyweb Holdings Limited | 
                    October 19, 2006</span></p>
              <p> The Wall Street Journal reports the growing popularity of Online communities among children, exploring the impact of virtual activities on a child's development and emphasizing the need for parental involvement.<font size="2" face="Arial"><a href="downloads/How-young-is-too-young-for-MySpace.pdf"></a> </font></p>
              <p><br>
                <a href="downloads/MySpace-For-The-Sandlot-Set.pdf">BusinessWeek Online - MySpace For The Sandlot Set</a>  (pdf)<br>
                <span class="sm_txt">businessweek.com | October 2, 2006</span><br>
                <br>
              A BuisnessWeek writer takes a look at the significance of social networking on children's chat based websites, highlighting Club Penguin as a leader in providing a safe environment for fun while Online.</p>
              <p align="right"><font size="2" face="Arial"><a href="downloads/MySpace-For-The-Sandlot-Set.pdf"></a></font></p>
